         <entry xml:id="antigrafa-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#anona-dlgenr"
                next="#antidiqos-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אנטיגרפא</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾnṭygrpʾ</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">anṭigrafaʾ</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנטיגרפה</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾnṭygrph</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">anṭigrafah</pron>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K V Ox1 Ox2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנטיגרפא</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="antigrafa-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">law</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">core borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">ad hoc formation</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false">Alexandria, Athens, Constantinople, Caesarea, Crete</usg>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>written reply</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Classical Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἀντιγραφή</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>אנטונינוס שלח לרבינו אמר ליה בגין דתיסווריה חסרין מה נעביד ונמלא יתהון, נסתיה לשליחא ואעליה לגו פרדיסה, שרי עקר פוגלין רברבין ושתל דקיקין, אמר ליה הב לי אנטיגרפין, אמר ליה לית את צריך, סלק לגביה אמר ליה הן היא אנטיגרפי, אמר ליה לא נתן לי כלום, ומה אמר לך, לא אמר לי כלום אלא נסתי ואעלי לפרדיסא שרי עקר פוגלין רברבין ושתל דקיקין, שרי מפיק דוכסין ומעייל דוכסין עד זמן דיתמלון תיסוורייא.</quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">67,6</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 761: 4; II 762: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">תיסווריה</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">תיסוורייא</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>Antoninus sent to our Teacher: ‘As our treasury is deficient, what shall we do to fill it?’ Thereupon he took his envoy, led him into his garden, bagan uprooting the large radishes and planted small ones in their place. ‘But give me a written reply,’ he requested. ‘You do not need it,’ was the reply. So he went back to him. ‘Where is the answer?’ demanded he. ‘He gave me nothing’, was the reply. ‘And what did he say to you?’ ‘Nothing at all, but he led me into his garden and began uprooting the large radishes and planting small ones.’ At that he began dismissing officers and replacing them with others, until his treasury was filled. (Freedman / Simon II 611)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">= <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 115 [35d: 54]</bibl>
                  </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Classical Greek</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3Da)ntigrafh%2F #antigrafa-dlgenr"
                        type="entry">ἀντιγραφή, A.</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
         Cf. <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 144a</bibl>, <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 68b-69a</bibl>; <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 108a</bibl>. <term xml:lang="jpa">אנטיגרפא</term> and <term xml:lang="jpa">אנטיגרפין</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾnṭygrgyn</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">antigrafin</term> from Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀντίγραφον</term> (as in EstR 7,24) should be distinguished between (<bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sokoloff, DJPA 41a</bibl>; <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 69a</bibl>; <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 108a</bibl>). However, <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 83a</bibl> doesn’t distinguish between the two, and neither does <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Shoval-Dudai 40b</bibl>. Cf. Syr. <term xml:lang="syc">ܐܢܛܝܓܪܦܐ</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾnṭygrpʾ</term> (<bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sokoloff, SL 61a</bibl>) [In SL, Sokoloff doesn’t distinguish between <term xml:lang="syc">ܐܢܛܝܓܪܦܐ</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾnṭygrpʾ</term> and <term xml:lang="syc">ܐܢܛܝܓܪܦܘܢ</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾnṭygrpwn</term>]. Cf. also <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sperber Card</bibl> ad loc.
      </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sokoloff, DJPA</title>
                  <citedRange>41a</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
